div1.p: Territory of Washington vs. C.H. Hutchingson } Judicial Warrant

To the sheriff or any constable of said County theras N.H. Harris has this day complained in writing under oath to the me of the Justice of the Peace in and for said County that J.H. Hutchinson did on the 31st day of October A.D. 1885 at said County did Fradulent courent 18 his own use two Hundred and fifty Dollars belonging to the said H.H. Harris. Therefore in the name of the United States you are commanded Forthwith to apprehend the said C.H. Hutchinson and bring him before me to the deal with according to law.
Given under my hand this 11th day of Nor.a.s. 1885
Alex Campbell Justice of the Peace
Territory of Washington Plaintif vs. Hutchinson Defendant
Justice of the Peace hereby authorizing W.H is aspecial Crustti execute this
Court Alex Camblell Justice of the Peace
FILED NOV 12 1885 James Seavey, Clerk By James P. Ludlow Deputy Clerk,
